{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"cost-items","type":"text","text":"# Cost Items (tcCostItem)\n**PURPOSE**: Master service catalog - the foundation of all pricing\n\n**WHY USED**: \n- Central repository of all services/products that can be charged\n- Standardizes pricing across all customers and jobs\n- Maintains consistency in service descriptions\n\n**HOW USED**:\n- Created by management as master templates\n- Classifications determine behavior:\n  - **Tool**: Links to physical assets in Load Out\n  - **Person**: Links to field personnel\n  - **Fleet**: Links to company vehicles/equipment\n  - **General/Other**: Miscellaneous services\n- **Flex**: Allows field price/discount overrides\n- **Calculated**: Auto-prices based on job total percentages\n- **Discountable**: Can apply customer discounts\n- Links to GL Accounts for accounting integration\n\n**KEY FEATURES**:\n- Default quantity minimums\n- Priority ordering for auto-add to tickets\n- Service Line categorization\n- Unit cost tracking for margin analysis","x":-520,"y":-640,"width":350,"height":300,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"price-books","type":"text","text":"# Price Books\n**PURPOSE**: Customer-specific pricing containers and contract management\n\n**WHY USED**: \n- Manage different pricing per customer/contract\n- Support complex pricing structures\n- Maintain pricing history and versions\n- Enable competitive pricing strategies\n\n**HOW USED**:\n**Structure Types**:\n- **Master Price Books**: Base pricing templates\n- **Child Price Books**: Customer-specific overrides\n- **Currency Support**: Multi-currency pricing\n- **Price Zones**: Geographic/market pricing differences\n\n**BUSINESS APPLICATIONS**:\n- Government vs. Private pricing\n- Volume discount contracts\n- Regional market pricing\n- Competitive bidding scenarios\n- Long-term contract management\n\n**FEATURES**:\n- Customer association management\n- Import/export pricing data\n- Bulk pricing updates\n- Expiry date management\n- Copy between price books\n- Audit trail of pricing changes","x":1240,"y":-880,"width":350,"height":300,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"load-out","type":"text","text":"# Load Out Items\n**PURPOSE**: Physical asset deployment and usage tracking\n\n**WHY USED**: \n- Track what equipment goes to which job\n- Link physical assets to billing charges\n- Asset utilization and availability management\n- Equipment maintenance and certification tracking\n\n**HOW USED**:\n**3 Categories**:\n1. **Assets**: Company-owned equipment with serial numbers\n2. **Third Party**: Rented/contracted equipment\n3. **Additional Items**: Miscellaneous materials/supplies\n\n**OPERATIONAL WORKFLOW**:\n1. Equipment checked out (DateOut, LocationOut)\n2. Deployed to job site\n3. Usage tracked with date stamps\n4. Equipment returned (DateIn, LocationIn)\n5. Can be flagged as \"Used\" for billing\n\n**INTEGRATION WITH BILLING**:\n- Copy selected items to Tickets\n- Automatically creates billing line items\n- Links Cost Items to physical assets\n- Tracks equipment vs. service charges\n\n**ASSET MANAGEMENT**:\n- Certification expiry tracking\n- Location and fleet assignment\n- Maintenance scheduling\n- Usage analytics for asset optimization","x":-560,"y":350,"width":350,"height":350,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"tickets","type":"text","text":"# Tickets (tcTicket)\n**PURPOSE**: Actual billable work performed - the money makers\n\n**WHY USED**: \n- Converts estimates/plans into actual billing\n- Tracks what was really done vs. planned\n- Creates audit trail for customer billing\n- Links physical work to financial records\n\n**HOW USED**:\n**3 Types with Different Workflows**:\n1. **Regular Tickets** (IsBid=false): Standard billable items\n2. **Bid Items** (IsBid=true): Require management approval before billing\n3. **Additional Items** (IsAdditional=true): Non-catalog emergency items\n\n**APPROVAL WORKFLOW**:\n- Bid Items need manager approval for cost overruns\n- Regular items auto-approved within limits\n- Additional items for unexpected work\n\n**RESOURCE LINKING**:\n- LoadOutID: Links to deployed equipment\n- JobFleetID: Links to company vehicles used\n- JobUserID: Links to personnel who did work\n- Creates complete work-to-billing audit trail\n\n**FINANCIAL INTEGRATION**:\n- Becomes invoice line items\n- Calculates taxes automatically\n- Tracks discounts and margins\n- GL Account integration for accounting","x":200,"y":120,"width":350,"height":350,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"workflow","type":"text","text":"# Business Workflow & Why It Matters\n\n**SETUP PHASE** (One-time):\n1. Create Cost Items (service catalog)\n2. Create Price Books (customer pricing)\n→ **Why**: Standardizes pricing, ensures consistency\n\n**SALES PHASE** (Per opportunity):\n3. Create Quotes from Cost Items\n4. Multiple quote versions for negotiations\n5. Customer approves final quote\n→ **Why**: Wins business, sets expectations\n\n**EXECUTION PHASE** (During work):\n6. Deploy Load Out items (equipment)\n7. Create/modify Tickets for actual work\n8. Bid Items require approval for overruns\n→ **Why**: Tracks real work vs. estimates\n\n**BILLING PHASE** (After work):\n9. Tickets become invoice line items\n10. Calculate taxes and totals\n11. Generate customer invoices\n→ **Why**: Gets paid for work performed\n\n**KEY BUSINESS RULES**:\n- Bid Items prevent cost overruns\n- Flex items allow field adjustments\n- Auto-calculated items scale with job size\n- Asset tracking links equipment to billing","x":1240,"y":590,"width":350,"height":400,"color":"2"},
		{"id":"system-intelligence","type":"text","text":"# System Intelligence & Automation\n\n**AUTO-CALCULATED PRICING**:\n- Cost Items can auto-price based on job totals\n- Percentage-based pricing (e.g., 15% of job total)\n- Min/Max price boundaries\n- Updates automatically as job scope changes\n→ **Why**: Ensures profitability on variable work\n\n**APPROVAL WORKFLOWS**:\n- Bid Items require management approval\n- Prevents field cost overruns\n- Maintains profit margins\n- Audit trail for decision making\n→ **Why**: Controls costs while allowing flexibility\n\n**ASSET-TO-BILLING INTEGRATION**:\n- Load Out automatically creates Tickets\n- Links physical equipment to charges\n- Prevents unbilled equipment usage\n- Tracks asset utilization\n→ **Why**: Maximizes revenue from asset deployment\n\n**PRICE CHANGE TRACKING**:\n- Flags when field prices differ from catalog\n- Tracks discount changes\n- Unit changes monitoring\n- Price book version control\n→ **Why**: Maintains pricing discipline and audit trails","x":1240,"y":1130,"width":350,"height":350,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"price-items","type":"text","text":"# Price Items (tcPriceItem)\n**PURPOSE**: Customer-specific pricing layer over Cost Items\n\n**WHY USED**: \n- Different customers need different rates\n- Contract-based pricing management\n- Price zone variations (geographic/market segments)\n- Maintains pricing history and changes\n\n**HOW USED**:\n- Created in Price Books for specific customers\n- Inherits Cost Item properties but overrides prices\n- Can be Active/Inactive per customer\n- Price Zones allow regional pricing differences\n- Used as templates when creating Tickets/Quotes\n\n**BUSINESS VALUE**:\n- Enables competitive pricing strategies\n- Supports contract negotiations\n- Maintains customer-specific rates\n- Tracks pricing changes over time\n- Ensures correct billing rates per contract","x":1240,"y":-440,"width":350,"height":300,"color":"2"},
		{"id":"quotes","type":"text","text":"# Quotes (tcQuote)\n**PURPOSE**: Pre-job customer proposals and estimates\n\n**WHY USED**: \n- Win new business with accurate pricing\n- Set customer expectations before work starts\n- Create multiple pricing scenarios\n- Document agreed-upon scope and pricing\n\n**HOW USED**:\n**Parent-Child Structure**:\n- **Quote Parent**: Named versions (\"Original\", \"Revised\", \"Final\")\n- **Quote Children**: Individual service line items\n- **Quote Additional**: Non-catalog estimate items\n\n**BUSINESS PROCESS**:\n1. Sales creates quote from Cost Items\n2. Multiple quote versions for negotiations\n3. Customer approves final quote\n4. Approved quotes copied to Tickets for actual work\n5. Variations tracked between quoted vs. actual\n\n**FEATURES**:\n- Currency conversion for international jobs\n- Copy to/from Tickets for easy comparison\n- PDF generation for customer presentation\n- Margin analysis for profitability\n- Tracks quote-to-close ratios","x":1240,"y":120,"width":350,"height":350,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"jobs","type":"text","text":"# Jobs\n**PURPOSE**: Central work order - the business transaction hub\n\n**WHY USED**: \n- Organizes all work activities under one umbrella\n- Links customer, location, timing, and pricing\n- Status workflow management (Quote→Active→Complete→Invoiced)\n- Central reporting and analytics point\n\n**HOW USED**:\n**Contains Everything**:\n- Customer and location information\n- Quotes for estimation phase\n- Tickets for actual billing\n- Load Out for equipment deployment\n- Job Log for operational tracking\n- Safety and quality records\n\n**WORKFLOW STAGES**:\n1. **Quote**: Initial estimation and proposal\n2. **Pending**: Approved, waiting to start\n3. **Active**: Work in progress\n4. **Complete**: Work finished\n5. **Invoiced**: Customer billed\n\n**BUSINESS INTELLIGENCE**:\n- Links to Price Book for customer rates\n- Revenue and margin calculation\n- Resource utilization tracking\n- Performance analytics\n- Customer profitability analysis","x":200,"y":830,"width":350,"height":300,"color":"1"}
